metadata.name: Kintsugi #91
metadata.description:
Kintsugi is a philosophy, it's the concept of highlighting imperfections, visualizing patches and seams on the area to focus on, rather than focusing on missing details.

This art of precious scars is a technique used as a means of analyzing the idea of ​​loss through synthesis and restoration of the destroyed and a metaphor for the possibility of rebirth.
Recovery from destructive events is possible through care and patching, not through hiding the damage, but by accepting a new state of the object or the whole life.
The world is a vase that is endlessly disassembled and sewn together again, continuing to bear traces of each event.

Non-human entities helped us put these vases together. In the beginning, there were vague forms, these were the shards themselves, created in collaboration with Latent Diffusion. Over time, they have grown in detail, drawing their stories more clearly, thanks to Jax Diffusion.

The code that puts everything together was written by Yulikolay, for which he is greatly appreciated.

metadata.name: Morixels Mans #863
metadata.description:
The Morixels Mans is unique Random Generated 10,000 PFP NFTs, and this collection is for people like me who are nostalgic for pixel arts.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 24 by 24 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution. 
The number of Traits in this collection is 12 (120 layers) and it has the ability to make 31,091,558,400 NFTs.
Some ​layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Ripped #90
metadata.description:
Ripped is a reflection on time and the temporary nature of lives lived.
It hints at past joys and experiences moved past and forgotten.
Ripped was created in p5.js, in a process of generating many different posters, inspired by generic and iconic poster images from the last century. After each one is meticulously designed, with many unique, randomly generated colours, shapes and texts. Then each one is ripped left, right, top and bottom until there is just a hint of what was there.
Stickers can be added with a mouse click.
Added stickers can be cleared with a 'c' key press.
Fonts used are all credited in the License.txt file.
Warning: The text is generated from code. There is a small possibility that offensive words may be generated in one language or another. This is not intentional and I apologise for any offence caused.

metadata.name: Shapes of the civilization #5
metadata.description:
In my first generative work, I put together two things about myself: my past and my present/future.
I combine my past as a construction worker, with more than a decade of experience, with my current present of 5 years, as a multimedia artist.

It took me a long time to build this project, there were countless restarts until I finally found the path I wanted to follow.
As a multimedia artist I always like to learn new techniques, and when I discovered fxhash I had no doubts, I wanted to learn creative coding, and this is the result of my work and dedication.

I used elements of architecture mixed with my greatest passion (and also where I spent most of my time until I delve into programming), oil painting!
The color palettes were inspired by some painters I admire, making this work even more special and personal.

In live mode: Press 's' to save as PNG (4800x4800)

Made with p5js and love.
May-June 2022

NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #885
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan
